{
  "answer": "**Bang-E-Dara Part 2** by Allama Iqbal, Chapter 9 (*Chaand aur Taare*).\n\nThe stars complain of weariness in shining to the moon,[^1] who replies on motion and stillness:\n\n> To pause upon this path is but a flaw,  \n> For hidden in Stillness is death's own law.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/09-chaand-aur-taare/translation/#p-6fe8f3).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/09-chaand-aur-taare/translation/#p-fb94a9).",
